article.headline: Pennsylvania 81, Dartmouth 59
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Tim Begley scored 18 points to lead four Pennsylvania players in double figures as the Quakers beat Dartmouth 81-59 Friday night to keep alive their hopes of a share of the Ivy League title. Begley was 7-of-11 from the floor, including four 3-point baskets. The victory kept Penn (16-9, 9-3 Ivy) two games behind Princeton, which defeated Harvard 60-51 to clinch a share of the title. The Tigers (11-1) can clinch the championship and the league's automatic NCAA bid Saturday night against Dartmouth. Penn shot 50 percent from the floor as Mark Zoller had 13 points, Jeff Schiffner 12 and Ibby Jaaber 10. Dartmouth (3-24, 1-12), losing its 17th straight, had 14 points by David Gardner and Leon Pattman.
